For the first time ever…

The Spencer Lodge Podcast takes Hollywood! 🇺🇸🎙

Joining the show to kick off this exclusive series is Sports & Celebrity Agent and advocate for addiction and mental health recovery: Darren Prince.

@Agent_DP represents icons like Magic Johnson, Charlie Sheen, Hulk Hogan, Carmen Electra, and many others.

But, behind his mega success, is a tragic story of childhood bullying, severe feelings of loneliness, substance abuse and an addiction problem…

In this honest and revealing conversation, Darren shares how he overcame the most challenging times of his life and found his purpose through this struggle.

Hit the link in my bio now to tune in.

With 2023 here it’s time I talk about what’s most important to me and those suffering with mental health and substance abuse issues. I suffered for 24 years with my opiate addiction only 5 people in my life new of in the end from the embarrassment and humiliation. Thanks to my man @jayshetty and all the other amazing platforms who have let me share my bottom to beginning story with over 14 years sober to help others see the light. It’s never too late to ask for help and find hope and recovery like I did. No need to suffer in silence as coming out of the dark into the light exists. #Hope #Peace #Recovery # Happiness

I’m posting this with nothing but gratitude in an effort to help someone suffering with mental health and substance abuse issues. This photo is on line with longtime dear friend and client @smokinjoefrazier sitting ringside at a Championship fight over 20 years ago with me being high on opiates. We live in a culture where too many are focused on external success and sadly we’ve seen so many people suffering the same way I did and much worse outcomes. You see most of our friends and family don’t see the signs especially if they don’t struggle with anxiety, depression and substance abuse issues themselves. You just never know what goes on between closed doors in anyone’s mind so be kind and of service more often. And if you’re suffering yourself speak up and ask for help that’s where the strength comes in and your darkest days can become the brightest of all lights. Today I celebrate 5300 days sober and have been through it all like loss of loved ones, clients, friends, surgeries, illness and business highs and lows. But the one thing I haven’t done due to my faith and recovery foundation is taken my will back. I’ve also developed real self esteem and self love internally on this spiritual sober journey by doing estimable acts. #Hope #Recovery #Peace #Happiness #Freedom #Blessed #Service.

So this is 53 today! What I've learned in all these years is people come and go but the real ones stay no matter if your on top of life or struggling. Always be of service and help others and never keep score. Don't hold onto resentments even for those who did wrong by you. Pray and forgive them because we deserve the peace to go on with our lives to manifest all the good. Let your past make you better not bitter. If you made a mistake show by your actions you were wrong. Take your pain and make it your greatest purpose! Don't ask GOD for success and material things only for good health, peace, safety and happiness for you and loved ones. If you're struggling with self-esteem start doing estimable acts as that will create the self love and confidence you've always been looking for. Don't compare your life to others on social media as most of what you're seeing is BS as everyone is struggling with something they won't put out there. And the best relationships in life happen when you least expect. Thx baby for the amazing cake ❤️ #BirthdayBoy #Happy #Peace #Serenity #Free #Recovered #DarrenPrince #thankyougod

I keep hearing about success and more success in business and branding but when are one of these networking events going to put an emphasis on mental health and substance abuse like I struggled with for 24 years? Coming up on 15 years sober I can tell you success and being “rich” have a totally definition to me now cause so many are hiding in secret like I was even at the height of business success. Internal peace, self love, self confidence from within and always being of service is what it’s about and took me a while to get here on this journey! My God Given message will resonate with any audience!  Peace #Happiness #Serenity #Recovery #spiritual

He now shares his story as a reminder to anyone that addiction doesn’t need to be the ending to your story.

Hard to believe it’s been 7 years since @muhammadali passed and almost 12 for @smokinjoefrazier. I was so blessed to work with and call both friends for 16 years though Joe was also like a second Father to me. Always so surreal seeing these pictures of these two 🤴’s sitting courtside at the @nba All-Star Game in 2002. Was such an honor to be there witnessing history. All of us are products of our childhood good and bad. I was one of the lucky ones to find my way out of a 24 year opiate addiction as I truly never felt comfortable in my own skin even with tremendous business success I had very low self esteem and self worth. The past 15 years on my recovery journey I’ve been able to heal and build that internal peace, love and happiness by doing acts of service, kindness and being vulnerable owning my truth. Truly nothing better then talking to kids today to not be like the young Darren Prince and speak up now and ask for help if you feel this way. Remember money and expensive things doesn’t make you successful from an internal sense if you’re not paying it forward as there are so many out there that justify success to avoid dealing with issues and character defects. Sadly this doesn’t allow people to live their best happiest lives as that was me most of my life till I was 38. #AimingHigh #DarrenPrince #Selflove #Peace #Happiness #serenity

It was 15 years ago today I surrendered to my 24 year drug addiction and double life. I fell to my knees in tears broken and beaten and begged God “Take the chains off me, take the money, take the business that I need a single day of freedom. I screamed if you take me out of hell I promise I’ll take others out with me”. A spiritual awakening then happened and my right shoulder was burning as I heard a voice say “I’ve got you and you’re ready” I then stood up and flushed the last of my opiates and went to a 12 step recovery meeting with the gift of desperation. I walked into a Church basement in NYC ego crushed and shared with these 150 people I was a drug addict that was suicidal and broken to the core and needed help. These spiritual brothers and sisters were all once of a hopeless state of mind and welcomed me with open arms as I felt a part of something for the first time in my life. Several came over to me and said I could do this one day at a time and told me they’d love me till I learned to love myself as long as I slowly worked through the 12 steps which were a bridge back to life. As I regained the power of choice and worked those steps and started being of service to others hope and recovery truly began. Now 15 years later I’ve kept my word to God taking many out of hell as I can’t keep this gift of recovery without giving it away. I’m blessed to have a platform around the world to be an agent of hope which means more to me than an agent in my career. I was accountable and blamed no one! I continue to be that way as healing and working on our character defects is an ongoing process for everyone. I developed self love from within and an unshakable faith, and the self esteem I was looking for my entire life doing estimable acts helping others. So many are struggling with mental health and substance abuse so please know hope and recovery exist and we can get through anything in life sober you just need the strength and courage to ask for help! My pain has now become my purpose and so can yours! #Hope #Recovery #Peace #Happiness #Freedom #Sobriety #Gratitude #AimingHighFoundation

Here I am a baby 👶🏼 DP. The older I get and the more spiritually connected I am I realize we’re all just big kids dealing with underlining character defects caused by traumas from childhood good and bad. We all have obstacles, challenges and breakthroughs we need to work through at all stages in life like my guys @vybadelicexperience and @davidgoggins always talk about. The truth is we never truly arrive and always need to dig down deep into our soul to keep getting to the next level of frequency if you want to live the most fulfilled life. The biggest key I’ve learned is it’s not what you can take from life but what you can give to others while not depleting your own positive energy. The best way to heal and thrive is to be of selfless service and pay it forward to others as often as possible as that’s where self love and self esteem is really built! #DarrenPrince #DP #Inspire #selfloveclub

Thx to my man @ericworre for the interview. Anyone who knows me knows this is 100% true. I look at money as something that brings tentative happiness. I’ve met and know many with generational wealth who deep down are miserable, deeply insecure and have no inner peace. Yes money allows us to take care of others buy homes,  travel and buy nice things which don’t get me wrong is great but that’s not what defines me. Being a voice of change to help others suffering with mental health and substance abuse has given me such a deeper meaning of wealth and what makes me who I am. I’ve developed real self love and self esteem not from things but from doing estimable acts for others. #Gratitude #Selflove #motivate #inspire #DarrenPrince

Yes a real angel showed up in my life in human form creating a life changing moment on July 2, 2008. Andrea Theodore you gave me the gift of life. Like you said in the most amazing hand written card you gifted me on my 1 year sober birthday. “Do I believe in miracles now because I am one”? “So long darkness, hello light, good by hopelessness hello hope and recovery” “No more hiding a double life now embrace the sunshine and guide others to and through it”. Here we are 15 1/2 years later doing that everyday while always working on sense of self and character defects! Self love and inner peace has never felt so good. For anyone suffering with mental health and substance abuse you all can turn your message into your message. I’m living proof thanks to God and others who have guided me on this one day at a time life changing journey! Humility has taught me don’t be impressed but what I do professionally be impressed by who I am personally. I work for some very special people that’s about it. #Peace #happiness #Serenity #Blessed #selflove
